This is most likely not a Mockito problem, but an issue of a wrong import statement:

* `java.awt.List` has a `getSize()` method returning an object of type `java.awt.Dimension`.

* `java.util.List` has a `size()` method returning an `int`.

A version with a correct import statement may look like this:

```java
import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertEquals;
import static org.mockito.Mockito.mock;
import static org.mockito.Mockito.when;

import java.util.List;
import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;

public class ListMockTest {

	@Test
	public void letsMockListClass() {
		List&lt;?&gt; listMock = mock(List.class);
		when(listMock.size()).thenReturn(2);
		assertEquals(2, listMock.size());
	}
}

```

